Milli-volts of thermopile in infrared thermometers in the Control or Reference plots. It typically varies between about -2.5 and +2.5 volts and it is proportional to the temperature difference between the target surface viewed by the IRT and the body temperature of the IRT. If it stays close to zero even when something hot or cold is held in front of the IRT, the IRT is bad.

PID variable scaled and limited to be within 0 to 10 volts. If you multiply this value by 10, you will have the percentage of full capacity the heaters are on.
Scada variable scaled to what is needed by SDM-CV04 to produce 0-10V output. For a CR1000 logger, this is simply multiplying PID_lmt by 1000, but some other loggers have an offset.
